#. type: Plain text
#: opensuse-leap-15-4
msgid ""
"Some code calls B<select>()  with all three sets empty, I<nfds> zero, and a "
"non-NULL I<timeout> as a fairly portable way to sleep with subsecond "
"precision."
msgstr ""
"Sommige code aanroept B<select>()  aan met alle drie verzamelingen leeg, "
"I<nfds> nul, en een niet-NULL I<tijdslimiet> als een enigszins overdraagbare "
"manier om met subseconde precisie te slapen."

#. type: Plain text
#: opensuse-leap-15-4
msgid ""
"On success, B<select>()  and B<pselect>()  return the number of file "
"descriptors contained in the three returned descriptor sets (that is, the "
"total number of bits that are set in I<readfds>, I<writefds>, I<exceptfds>)  "
"which may be zero if the timeout expires before anything interesting "
"happens.  On error, -1 is returned, and I<errno> is set to indicate the "
"error; the file descriptor sets are unmodified, and I<timeout> becomes "
"undefined."
msgstr ""
"On success, B<select>()  and B<pselect>()  return the number of file "
"descriptors contained in the three returned descriptor sets (that is, the "
"total number of bits that are set in I<readfds>, I<writefds>, I<exceptfds>) "
"dat nul kan zijn indien de tijdslimiet overschrijdt voor dat er iets "
"interessant gebeurd. Bij een fout wordt -1 teruggegeven en I<errno> wordt "
"overeenkomstig gezet; de bestandsindicator verzamelingen blijven "
"ongewijzigd, en I<timeout> wordt ongedefinieerd."

#. type: Plain text
#: opensuse-leap-15-4
msgid ""
"B<select>()  conforms to POSIX.1-2001, POSIX.1-2008, and 4.4BSD "
"(B<select>()  first appeared in 4.2BSD).  Generally portable to/from non-BSD "
"systems supporting clones of the BSD socket layer (including System\\ V "
"variants).  However, note that the System\\ V variant typically sets the "
"timeout variable before exit, but the BSD variant does not."
msgstr ""
"B<select>() voldoet aan POSIX.1-2001, POSIX.1-2008, en 4.4BSD (B<select>()  "
"verscheen voor het eerst in 4.2BSD). Is in het algemeen overdraagbaar naar/"
"van niet-BSD systemen die klonen van de BSD socket laag ondersteunen "
"(inclusief System\\ V varianten). Hoewel, de System\\ V variant typisch de "
"tijdslimiet variabelen zetten voor terugkeer, en de BSD variant dat niet "
"doet. "

#. type: Plain text
#: opensuse-leap-15-4
msgid ""
"Concerning the types involved, the classical situation is that the two "
"fields of a I<timeval> structure are typed as I<long> (as shown above), and "
"the structure is defined in I<E<lt>sys/time.hE<gt>>.  The POSIX.1 situation "
"is"
msgstr ""
"Betreffende de betrokken typen is de klassieke situatie dat twee velden in "
"een I<timeval> structure worden getypeerd als I<long> (zoals hierboven "
"getoond), en de structure zoals gedefinieerd in I<E<lt>sys/time.hE<gt>>.  De "
"POSIX.1 situatie is"

#. type: Plain text
#: opensuse-leap-15-4
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"struct timeval {\n"
"    time_t         tv_sec;     /* seconds */\n"
"    suseconds_t    tv_usec;    /* microseconds */\n"
"};\n"
msgstr ""
"struct timeval {\n"
"    time_t         tv_sec;     /* seconden */\n"
"    suseconds_t    tv_usec;    /* microseconden */\n"
"};\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: opensuse-leap-15-4
msgid ""
"where the structure is defined in I<E<lt>sys/select.hE<gt>> and the data "
"types I<time_t> and I<suseconds_t> are defined in I<E<lt>sys/types.hE<gt>>."
msgstr ""
"waar de structure is gedefinieerd in I<E<lt>sys/select.hE<gt>> en de data "
"types I<time_t> en I<suseconds_t> zijn gedefinieerd in I<E<lt>sys/types."
"hE<gt>>."

#. type: Plain text
#: opensuse-leap-15-4
msgid ""
"Concerning prototypes, the classical situation is that one should include "
"I<E<lt>time.hE<gt>> for B<select>().  The POSIX.1 situation is that one "
"should include I<E<lt>sys/select.hE<gt>> for B<select>()  and B<pselect>()."
msgstr ""
"Betreffende prototypen is de klassieke situatie dat men I<E<lt>time.hE<gt>>  "
"moet gebruiken voor B<select>(). De POSIX.1 situatie is dat men I<E<lt>sys/"
"select.hE<gt>> moet gebruiken voor B<select>() en B<pselect>()."

#. type: Plain text
#: opensuse-leap-15-4
msgid ""
"Under glibc 2.0, I<E<lt>sys/select.hE<gt>> gives the wrong prototype for "
"B<pselect>().  Under glibc 2.1 to 2.2.1, it gives B<pselect>()  when "
"B<_GNU_SOURCE> is defined.  Since glibc 2.2.2, the requirements are as shown "
"in the SYNOPSIS."
msgstr ""
"Onder glibc 2.0 geeft  I<E<lt>sys/select.hE<gt>> het verkeerde prototype "
"voor B<pselect>(). Onder glibc 2.1 tot 2.2.1 geeft het B<pselect>() zodra "
"B<_GNU_SOURCE> is gedefinieerd. Vanaf glibc 2.2.2 zijn de vereisten zoals "
"getoond in SAMENVATTING"

